Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE Agribusiness is pleased to present for sale the Elgin Valley Vineyard holdings of Accolade Wines Australia Limited and Gartner Farms SE Pty Ltd.
Together the holdings represent a substantial 142.86* hectares of vineyard occupying a total land area of approximately 227 hectares. 
Individually the holdings are broken out as follows:
•	Accolade - Allotment 1 D38681, 82* hectares in total with approximately 48 hectares planted.
•	Gartner - Allotments 21 DP4571 & 33 D86314, 149* hectares in total with approximately 95 hectares planted.
The two holdings are being marketed for sale concurrently; however potential investors are being offered the alternative of purchasing either holding separately.
Situated in the Limestone Coast Region of South Australia, Elgin Valley Vineyard is only 15* kilometres from the coastline of the Southern Ocean, and in proximity to the world renowned Coonawarra Wine Region. 
Situated in the Limestone Coast Region of South Australia, Elgin Valley Vineyard is only 15* kilometres from the coastline of the Southern Ocean, and in proximity to the world renowned Coonawarra Wine Region. Planted to a mix of cool climate red and white varieties that include Shiraz, Cabernet Sauvignon, Pinot Noir, Chardonnay and Sauvignon Blanc, the holdings present a unique opportunity to acquire production capacity in a period of strengthening demand.
The Elgin Valley Vineyard holdings are being offered on a walk in walk out basis. 
KEY FEATURES 
The key features of the Properties can be summarized as follows: 
Substantial vineyard holding located within proximity to the world renowned Coonawarra Region. 
Benefited by a unique terroir - maritime climate producing dry summers, cool winters and reliable (winter) rainfall combined with sandy loam soils over soft limestone. 
Highly productive holdings feature a range or red and white cool climate varietals. 
Secure access to a regulated water system and high winter rainfall; provide risk mitigation against climate variability. 

The Properties are being offered for sale via a public Expression of Interest campaign, closing Monday 20 November 2017 at 5pm ACDT.
